# Layer-0 PII-scan exemptions (pathspec patterns), consumed by .git/hooks/pre-commit.
#
# These are PUBLIC-BY-LAW legal-disclosure pages. An Austrian Impressum must
# show the GISA-Zahl (8-digit, trips the phone-like check) and a business
# contact email (trips the email check) per §5 ECG / §63 GewO / §25 MedienG.
# The personal phone number is deliberately omitted (see ai-brain 00g). The
# Layer-0 guard stays active across the rest of the repo.
src/components/LegalImpressumDE.tsx
src/components/LegalImpressumEN.tsx
src/components/LegalPrivacyDE.tsx
src/components/LegalPrivacyEN.tsx

# All documentation — specs, plans, offer/landing copy, brand notes. These
# intentionally carry GISA/contact references, native currency amounts, and
# date/ID digit runs by design (internal/by-design surfaces, not shipped code).
# Exempt the whole tree so new docs (docs/superpowers/, docs/offers/, …) are
# never missed. Trade-off: the email/phone/deny-name scan is also off under
# docs/ — acceptable for internal docs. The Layer-0 guard stays active elsewhere.
docs/

# Contact API route hardcodes the studio's own PUBLIC recipient address
# (the same hallo@ business inbox published on the Impressum) as the
# sendMail destination — not third-party PII.
src/app/api/contact/route.ts

# Footer renders the studio's own PUBLIC business address as a visible mailto
# (the same hallo@ inbox on the Impressum and in the Organization schema) — a
# low-friction contact point, not third-party PII.
src/components/Footer.tsx

# Single source of truth for the two productized entry offers (Website-Check +
# Direktbucher) and their public fixed prices. Imported by HomeOffers, by
# BlogOfferCta, and by the blog generator's linter. Same rationale as above:
# prices are intentional public marketing figures, isolated to this one module
# (not the shared copy dictionary), so the Layer-0 currency/PII scan stays
# active over all other site copy.
#
# This entry replaces three older ones. HomeOffers.tsx no longer needs an
# exemption because the amounts have left it, and WebsiteCheck.tsx /
# WebsiteCheckJsonLd.tsx were deleted by #118 when the offers moved to the werk
# storefront — an allow entry for a path that no longer exists silently
# pre-exempts anything later created there, which inverts the guard.
src/lib/offers.mjs

# Machine-readable studio summary for AI assistants and agents. Carries the
# public hallo@ inbox and the Präsenz entry price — the same figures already
# published on the werk storefront it points at. Intentionally readable.
public/llms.txt

# Site layout emits the Organization + LocalBusiness JSON-LD, which now carries
# the public business telephone (the same number on the Impressum + footer) for
# NAP consistency. The digit run trips the phone-like guard; it is the studio's
# own published contact number, not third-party PII.
src/app/(site)/[locale]/layout.tsx
